.SH NAME
sync  \- commit buffer cache to disk.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <unistd.h>
.B int sync(void);
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sync()
first commits inodes to buffers, and then buffers to disk.
It always returns 0.
